#Notes on titles for those that look into this history file for India Kingdom stuff. Technically many of the 'smaller' Kingdoms of India were ruled by a 'Raja' and not a 'Maharaja' and thus flavorization for most Indian cultures makes dukes into Raja's and Kingdoms into Maharaja's. But at the same time they were actual Kings/Kingdoms and had actual courts which they won't get with just a duchy. Plus giving them Kingdoms (and, at times, de jure land) also makes them less likely to be instantly gobbled up via de jure wars as many managed to outlive their larger neighbors by centuries. 

###START BENGAL###
